    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "DTC Commentary: P1297"
    },
    {
      "type": "dtc",
      "code": "P1297",
      "text": "DTC P1297: ELD voltage low"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Detection principle explanation"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "67_3.0_jpn_11394338_4.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The ELD is built into the relay box and monitors the current flowing from the 12V battery and transmits it to the PGM-FI ECU. if the ELD output voltage remains below a predetermined value for a predetermined period of time, the PGM-FI ECU judges a failure and stores a DTC."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Detection frequency, detection sequence, detection time required, detection method type, OBD status"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "rows": [
        [
          {
            "text": "Detection frequency"
          },
          {
            "text": "24-hour (e.g. observation, operation (of a machine), care (of patient))"
          }
        ],
        [
          {
            "text": "Detection order (of the DTC in question)"
          },
          {
            "text": "nashi (Pyrus pyrifolia, esp. var. culta)"
          }
        ],
        [
          {
            "text": "Detection time"
          },
          {
            "text": "5.0 seconds or longer"
          }
        ],
        [
          {
            "text": "Detection method type"
          },
          {
            "text": "2D/C (2 consecutive detection method), PGM-FI warning light: off"
          }
        ],
        [
          {
            "text": "OBD Status"
          },
          {
            "text": "Normal judgment, failure judgment, not completed"
          }
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
